From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2025 12:07:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi:ath12k: Build new regd after AFC
 payload

Create a new regd for updation to the kernel wiphy after processing
the AFC payload. Copy the 2.4 GHz and 5GHz regulatory rules and
non-SP 6 GHz rules from the existing regd and use the new AFC payload
to generate the 6 GHz SP rules.

The SP rule here is the coalesced, HW frequency limited, 20 MHz
boundary aligned AFC frequency ranges which are also present in the
AFC payload channel object. Also, include the generated NO_IR
rules for those frequencies which are not present in the AFC payload
but are present in the country SP regulatory rules. Both the SP
rules and NO_IR rules are added in the increasing order of
frequencies.

Improve code readability by modularizing the API
'ath12k_reg_process_afc_power_event' into individual functions:
   - To check for AFC payload validity,
   - To generate the SP rules and NO_IR rules,
   - To update the wiphy with the new regd.

